editCommitPoly(25.10)                                    editCommitPoly(25.10)

Name
       editCommitPoly  - Ends a newly created polygon at the specified coordi-
       nates

Syntax
       editCommitPoly

       [-help]

       <point>

       Ends a newly created polygon at the  specified  coordinates.  Use  this
       command after at least one editAddPoly command has been issued.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editCommitPoly parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editCommitPoly

       <point>
              Specifies  the  x and y coordinates for the end point of a newly
              created wire polygon.

Example
              * The following commands create a three-sided wire polygon  that
                ends at the point specified by editCommitPoly.

                editAddPoly 700 300

                editAddPoly 700 500

                editCommitPoly 200 400

                The first side of the wire polygon starts at 700, 300 and ends
                at  700,  500.  The second side starts at 700, 500 and ends at
                200, 400. The third side is formed  by  joining  the  starting
                point  of the polygon (700,300) and the ending point specified
                by editCommitPoly (200,400).

